<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="912" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d912">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 Bandit Activities/469:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HL1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Higgins</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-12T18:00:00-04:00">July 12,
                                    1932—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>29. Your 58, July 10, 9 a.m. In your discussion with the President you
                            may omit reference to the points mentioned in the last two sentences of
                            the penultimate paragraph of the Department’s instruction No. 305 of
                            July 1.</p>
                        <p>Department approves your suggestion as to the specific measures which you
                            should propose that the President carry out in an effort to improve the
                            situation on the frontier.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>